article.headline: Wofford 67, Coll. of Charleston 66
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Corey Godzinski scored a career-high 15 points and had the game-winning dunk with 1.9 seconds left as Wofford edged the College of Charleston 67-66 on Monday. Drew Gibson added 10 points and one of his six assists was on the winning bucket as the Terriers (12-8, 5-5 Southern Conference) won their fourth straight by scoring the game's final six points. Scott Dustin had 19 points and eight rebounds and Andrew Goudelock and Tony White Jr. scored 13 points apiece for the Cougars (9-11, 4-6), who were outrebounded by 12. White's 3-pointer with 2:26 left put the College of Charleston ahead 66-61, but the Cougars never scored again. White missed the front end of a 1-and-1 with 11 seconds left before Godzinski's dunk. Goudelock missed a desperation 3-point attempt at the buzzer.
